com.wizzer.mle.parts.j2d.props

Interface IMlePropPart

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IImageProperty

    public interface IMlePropPart
    This class provides a common interface for Magic Lantern properties.

    The interface provides a common mechanism for property values to be transported between objects in the Magic Lantern Runtime Engine. In general, the methods provided by IMlePropPart are used by Actors to communicate with their respective Roles.

    Author:
    Mark S. Millard

    • Method Detail

      • push

        boolean push(com.wizzer.mle.runtime.core.IMleObject obj)
      throws com.wizzer.mle.runtime.core.MleRuntimeException
        Push the property value to a corresponding element in the system. The object implementing this interface inherently knows how the property value will be pushed.
        Parameters:
        obj - The Magic Lantern object containing the properties being pushed. In most cases, this will be a MleActor.
        Returns:
        true is returned if the property was successfully pushed. Otherwise, false will be returned.
        Throws:
        com.wizzer.mle.runtime.core.MleRuntimeException - This exception is thrown if an error occurs whil pushing the property value.

        boolean pull(com.wizzer.mle.runtime.core.IMleObject obj)
      throws com.wizzer.mle.runtime.core.MleRuntimeException
        Pull the property value from a corresponding element in the system. The object implementing this interface inherently knows how the property value will be pulled.
        Parameters:
        obj - The Magic Lantern object containing the properties being updated. In most cases, this will be a MleActor.
        Returns:
        true is returned if the property was successfully pulled. Otherwise, false will be returned.
        Throws:
        com.wizzer.mle.runtime.core.MleRuntimeException - This exception is thrown if an error occurs whil pulling the property value.
